&gt; &gt;
&gt; &gt; On the specs side, the MiniBox has controls for both scan rate as 
&gt; well
&gt; &gt; as sensitivity, so you can cut down on the amount of random noise 
&gt; and
&gt; &gt; also find a speed which seems clearer, whereas you cannot with the 
&gt; RS
&gt; &gt; Hack (as far as I know). The rechargeable battery lasts about 40-50
&gt; &gt; hours on one charge... nothing to replace that way. It has both a
&gt; &gt; speaker output and one for a recorder so you can not only hear it as
&gt; &gt; loud as you like, but you can directly record your session from the 
&gt; box.  
&gt; &gt; 
&gt; &gt; When it comes to audible differences, the quality of the electronics
&gt; &gt; used provides clearer sound. I am not straining so much to hear
&gt; &gt; things. It is just speculation on my part, but it seems to take less
&gt; &gt; time and less effort for communication from the other side to come
&gt; &gt; through with the Mini. At least, in my experiences with both 
&gt; devices.
&gt; &gt; Though, I have gotten snippets from the RS Hack that were 
&gt; impressive.
